y, Aberdeenshire, Scotland, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"de","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Dilip, Anirban, Gopal, Alok, Anindya, Arunava, Asit, Asok, Dibyendu, Goutam, Indra, Indranil.","Indian: variant of   Dey  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Dey","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Indian Ashit, Indu, Naina, Partha, Soumya, Ajit, Anjan, Anjana, Anup, Arjun, Arun, Ashim.","English, Scottish, and Welsh: variant of   Day  .","German: topographic name from a field name in North Rhine-Westphalia, denoting a sizeable piece of land, from Middle Low German <i>dē</i> ‘thigh’ (referring to the shape of the property)."]}]},{"name":"Gordon","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from Gordon in Berwickshire, named with Welsh <i>gor</i> ‘spacious’ + <i>din</i> ‘fort’.","English (of Norman origin): habitational name from Gourdon in Saône-et-Loire, so called from the Gallo-Roman personal name <i>Gordus</i> + the locative suffix <i>-o</i>, <i>-ōnis</i>.","English (of Norman origin): alternatively, said to be a nickname from a diminutive of Old French <i>gourd</i> ‘heavy, dull, sluggish’ (compare 8 below)."],"variants":[{"name":"Gordin","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Jewish Eyal, Moisey, Yakov, Zalman, Erez, Faina, Haya, Mendel.  Russian Leonid, Aleksandr, Boris, Feiga, Genady.","Jewish (from Russia): variant of   Gordon   5.","French: variant of   Gourdin  . This surname is very rare in France."]},{"name":"Gordan","meanings":["German: variant of   Jordan  . The surname <i>Gordan</i> is very rare in Germany.","Irish (Wexford and Sligo): adopted as an Anglicized form of <b>Mag Mhuirneacháin</b> ‘son of <i>Muirneachán</i>’, a personal name from a diminutive of <i>muirneach</i> ‘lovable’."]}]},{"name":"Adam","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Biblical.  See  <b>Adam</b> ."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Adam de Gordon 6th Laird of Gordon was born in 1254, in Huntly, Aberdeenshire, Scotland, United Kingdom, his father, Sir Adam de Gordon, 5th Laird of Gordon, was 34 and his mother, Lady Alicia Gordon, was 20. He married Marjorie McDuff in 1272, in Stitchill, Roxburghshire, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 1 son. He registered for military service in 1296. He died on 28 April 1296, in Dunbar, Haddingtonshire, Scotland, at the age of 42, and was buried in Scotland."},"et":{"1254–28 April 1296":"1254–28. aprill 1296","1254–1296":"1254–1296","1255–1296":"1255–1296","1273–1333":"1273–1333","1220–1270":"1220–1270","1234–1280":"1234–1280","1234":"1234","1333":"1333","1255":"1255","1254":"1254","1220":"1220","1296":"1296","1273":"1273","1272":"1272","28 April 1296":"28. aprill 1296","1270":"1270","1280":"1280","Stitchill, Roxburghshire, Schotland":"Stitchill, Roxburghshire, Scotland","Huntley, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Huntly, Aberdeenshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom","Dunbar, Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Dunbar, Haddingtonshire, Scotland","Carthage, Tunis, Tunisia":"Carthage, Tunis, Tuneesia","Gordon, Berwickshire, Scotland":"Gordon, Berwickshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Huntly, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Huntly, Aberdeenshire, Šotimaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1254–28 April 1296":"1254–28. huhtikuuta 1296","1254–1296":"1254–1296","1255–1296":"1255–1296","1273–1333":"1273–1333","1220–1270":"1220–1270","1234–1280":"1234–1280","1234":"1234","1333":"1333","1255":"1255","1254":"1254","1220":"1220","1296":"1296","1273":"1273","1272":"1272","28 April 1296":"28. huhtikuuta 1296","1270":"1270","1280":"1280","Stitchill, Roxburghshire, Schotland":"Stitchill, Roxburghshire, Scotland","Huntley, Aberdeenshire, Scotland":"Huntly, Aberdeenshire, Skotlanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Dunbar, Haddingtonshire, Scotland":"Dunbar,